text: How do founder(s) possibly own 15-20% of a company after all the fundraising stages - after several rounds of dilution and creating large employee option pool that an investor insists on? Spoke to a few founders over the last month, couple of them who went to build large companies only to own a lot less than <<10% of the company. Sensed sadness - considering it's your life's work. Any better solution for future founders?
